72.name: Total population (Gapminder & UN)
72.description: Population by country, available from 1800 to 2019 based on Gapminder data and UN Population Division (2017) estimates.

source.name: Population by country, 1800 to 2100 (Gapminder & UN)
source.dataPublishedBy: Gapminder and United Nations Population Division (2017)
source.additionalInfo:
Gapminder dataset. Available online at http://www.gapminder.org/.

Population data by country is taken from Version 5 of Gapminder. This provides data by country from 1800 through to 2100.

From 1950 to 2015, estimates come from the UN Population Revision (2017), and projections to 2100 from the UN Population Revision (2017) medium scenario.

Full documentation of Gapminder's sources and process are available here: https://www.gapminder.org/data/documentation/gd003/.

UN population revision citation:
United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2017). World Population Prospects: The 2017 Revision, DVD Edition. Available at: https://esa.un.org/unpd/wpp/Download/Standard/Population/.

349.name: Life satisfaction in Cantril Ladder (World Happiness Report 2019)
349.description: Average of survey responses to the 'Cantril Ladder' question in the Gallup World Poll. The survey question asks respondents to think of a ladder, with the best possible life for them being a 10, and the worst possible life being a 0.

source.name: World Happiness Report (2019)
source.dataPublisherSource: Gallup World Poll surveys (life evaluation question)
source.additionalInfo: Life evaluation was measured by the individual answers to the Cantril ladder question: “Please imagine a ladder, with steps numbered from 0 at the bottom to 10 at the top. The top of the ladder represents the best possible life for you and the bottom of the ladder represents the worst possible life for you. On which step of the ladder would you say you personally feel you stand at this time?”
